---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '@/components/Hero.astro';
import CTABlock from '@/components/CTABlock.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What is Lush Kitchen?"
  description="An explainer on the Lush Kitchen subscription box: exclusive products, returning favourites, and a passionate community of subscribers."
>
  <Hero
    title="What is Lush Kitchen?"
    tag="For the uninitiated"
    minimal
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <div class="page-content" data-animate="stagger-children">
        <p>
          New to Kitchen? Here's everything you need to know about the Lush Kitchen subscription box.
        </p>

        <h3>The short version</h3>
        <p>
          Lush Kitchen is a monthly subscription box from Lush. Subscribers pay a set price, and every
          month a box arrives with a mix of exclusive products, returning favourites, and sometimes
          completely new experimental items. There's no choosing what's inside, and that's half the fun.
        </p>

        <h3>What's actually in the box?</h3>
        <p>
          Usually 4–6 products. Could be bath bombs, bubble bars, shower gels, soaps, body lotions —
          basically anything Lush makes. Some months lean harder into bath products, some months are
          more body care focused. The mix changes and that's what keeps it interesting.
        </p>
        <p>
          The exciting part is that many of these products are Kitchen exclusives — unavailable anywhere
          else. Some are brand new creations, some are discontinued fan favourites brought back for one
          more run. Long-time fans will remember the old Kitchen before it was a subscription, where
          products were voted on and ordered individually. Different era, same energy.
        </p>

        <h3>The community</h3>
        <p>
          The Kitchen community is one of the best parts of subscribing. Subscribers swap scent notes,
          debate which month was the strongest, and get genuinely excited when a discontinued favourite
          comes back. It's not performative — people just really love this stuff.
        </p>
        <p>
          There's a real thing that happens when a product from years ago turns up in a box and
          everyone collectively loses it. That shared nostalgia is what makes Kitchen special.
        </p>

        <h3>Is it worth subscribing?</h3>
        <p>
          The Kitchen subscription has been running since February 2022, and the quality has been
          consistently strong. Some boxes are standouts, some are quieter, but even the lighter months
          tend to have at least one product that surprises. The element of surprise is genuinely addictive.
        </p>
        <p>
          For anyone considering it: most long-time subscribers say it's worth it, even if a product
          or two each month gets gifted to friends. The ones that land become instant favourites.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABlock
    title="Browse the archive"
    description="Monthly Kitchen boxes since 2022, with products, scent notes, and nostalgia."
    primaryLink="/kitchen-boxes/"
    primaryLabel="Kitchen Box Archive"
    secondaryLink="/about/"
    secondaryLabel="About"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-content h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .page-content p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    max-width: none;
  }
</style>
